result.execSummary:
The defendant Elliott T Johnson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Elliott T Johnson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Elliott T Johnson was found guilty of False Imprisonment, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.30.
  • Elliott T Johnson was found guilty of Intentionally Sell Dang. Weapon to Child, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.60(2)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

SIGNATURE BOND SET - REFERRAL TO BMP
 - The court orders a Signature Bond in the amount of $5,000 per case,on the condition that the defendant reports to, and complies with, Dane County Bail Monitoring (DCBM).  The defendant shall be released only on a weekday between the hours of 8:00a.m.-3:00p.m. and shall report to DCBM immediately upon his release from jail. 
- Defendant shall comply with all rules of BMP including random drug testing.
- If defendant fails to comply with DCBM, cash bail is automatically set in the amount of $5,000 (per case), as higher cash bail is necessary to assure appearance in court. BMP is removed as condition of bond.
- Defendant shall be in his residence betwn 8:00 p.m. & 6:00 a.m. unless at or traveling to or from school, treatment or employment as approved by BMP.
- Defendant shall not use or possess controlled substances or drug paraphernalia without a valid prescription.
- Defendant shall not have any contact, direct or indirect, with D.R.J. or his mother.
- Defendant shall not be in the 900 Blk of W Badger Rd, Madison.
- Defendant shall not possess any type of dangerous weapon.
